result.execSummary:
The defendant Jameson R Myers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 1:39 pm [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Michael Malmstadt presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Jameson R Myers in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa. DA Susan V. Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On Motion of the State, the Court amends Count #1 to Possession of a Controlled Substance, THC, without a valid prescription contrary 961.41(3g)(e), a misdemeanor

Constitutional rights given; plea of "Guilty" entered on Count #1; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Count #2

On Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:
--Cooperate with any AODA Program, per Agent
--Maintain absolute sobriety
--No alcohol, no mood altering durgs or controlled substances w/o a valid prescription
--Take all prescribed medications as prescribed
--Random urinalyses
--To obtain/maintain employment and/or education program, per Agent
